Ask HN: Collection of Clever Scams
text:
Recently watched a video from JerryRigEverything on a typical Youtube-comment scam (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iROF9Dd7FXA).

Would love to see a collection of clever scams you have come across so that it might become easier to spot them in real life and understand how they work.

This is how the mentioned scam from JerryRigEverything works:

- bad actor chooses Youtube channel with large following and possibly trusted relationship between channel-creator and viewers

- bad actor creates fake profile imitating YT channel (same profile pic, etc)

- bad actor replies to comments using fake profile claiming viewers have won something (e.g. iPhone 14 Pro) and that they should contact them via Telegram

- once chat on Telegram is initiated between bad actor and viewer the viewer believes they are chatting with the real Youtuber

- chit-chat followed by mentioning the gift again (e.g. iPhone 14) and asking viewer for shipping address

- then asking viewer to cover shipping costs (actual scam)

- then never sending anything to the viewer
